This paper discusses the use of data mining techniques to detect fraudulent accounts, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of Bayesian Classification and Association Rule, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data mining (cs.DS) respectively. The detection of fraudulent accounts involves analyzing patterns in transactions, which can be seen as a database problem (cs.DB). Finally, the paper mentions the use of the system for financial institutions, which could involve information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques for accessing and analyzing financial data.
